documentation.xhtml:p: Retroreflective sensors are active low which means that the signal goes from 1 to 0 when the sensor is triggered by the pallet

content.xhtml:p:
- The conveyor belt will turn off once a pallet reaches the front of the turntable or when a pallet stops blocking retroreflective sensor 1 and retroreflective sensor 0 is blocked. It will also turn off when a pallet reaches the back turntable sensor so that a pileup does not occur.
- It will not start up again until the pallet passes completely through retroreflective sensor 2 indicating that it has left the turntable and is remembered using RS2
The SmallBox signal goes high when a pallet first blocks retroreflective sensor 1 and a box blocks Light Array 7. It is reset when the pallet first passes through retroreflective sensor 2.

The turntable starts rolling objects forward when a pallet reaches retroreflective sensor 1 and the conveyor belt is at 0 degrees or when the turntable has rotated 90 degrees and there is a small box on it. This only happens if the emergency stop is not engaged.
It turns off when a pallet reaches the front of the turntable, on Factory IO reset or the Emergency Stop is pressed

The turntable will rotate to the 90-degree position when there is a small box, and the turntable has stopped moving the pallet. This is stored in a separate latch to prevent the turntable rotating in an oscillating manner.
This is combination with the pallet reaching the front of the turntable causes it to rotate. The turntable rotates back to 0 degrees once the pallet has left the turntable or on a Factory IO reset.
The second conveyor will turn on when a Small Box is detected, and the Turntable has rotated to the 90-degree position. It turns off when the pallet has gone into the receiver and disappeared.
!!! Check this RetroReflect2 connection in case of issues with the turntable turning.
